2026-05-16 09:04:59 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #1 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] submit_repaired_code({"code": "import zipfile\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\npath = Path('kramabench-biomedical-hard-4/files/1-s2.0-S0092867420301070-mmc4.xlsx')\n\nNS = {'main': 'http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/spreadsheetml/2006/main',\n      'rel': 'http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/package/2006/relationships'}\n\n\ndef col_to_index(col):\n    n = 0\n    for ch in col:\n        n = n * 26 + (ord(ch.upper()) - ord('A') + 1)\n    return n - 1\n\n\nwith zipfile.ZipFile(path, 'r') as z:\n    shared_strings = []\n    if 'xl/sharedStrings.xml' in z.namelist():\n        root = ET.fromstring(z.read('xl/sharedStrings.xml'))\n        for si in root.findall('main:si', NS):\n            texts = [t.text or '' for t in si.findall('.//main:t', NS)]\n            shared_strings.append(''.join(texts))\n\n    wb = ET.fromstring(z.read('xl/workbook.xml'))\n    rels = ET.fromstring(z.read('xl/_rels/workbook.xml.rels'))\n    rel_map = {\n        rel.attrib['Id']: rel.attrib['Target']\n        for rel in rels.findall('rel:Relationship', NS)\n    }\n\n    readme_target = None\n    for sheet in wb.findall('main:sheets/main:sheet', NS):\n        if sheet.attrib.get('name') == 'README':\n            rid = sheet.attrib.get('{http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/relationships}id')\n            readme_target = rel_map[rid]\n            break\n\n    if readme_target is None:\n        print('README sheet not found')\n    else:\n        sheet_path = 'xl/' + readme_target.lstrip('/')\n        sheet_root = ET.fromstring(z.read(sheet_path))\n\n        rows = []\n        for row in sheet_root.findall('.//main:sheetData/main:row', NS):\n            values = {}\n            max_col = -1\n            for c in row.findall('main:c', NS):\n                ref = c.attrib.get('r', '')\n                m = re.match(r'([A-Z]+)', ref)\n                if not m:\n                    continue\n                col_idx = col_to_index(m.group(1))\n                max_col = max(max_col, col_idx)\n                cell_type = c.attrib.get('t')\n                value = ''\n                if cell_type == 's':\n                    v = c.find('main:v', NS)\n                    if v is not None and v.text is not None:\n                        value = shared_strings[int(v.text)]\n                elif cell_type == 'inlineStr':\n                    value = ''.join(t.text or '' for t in c.findall('.//main:t', NS))\n                else:\n                    v = c.find('main:v', NS)\n                    if v is not None and v.text is not None:\n                        value = v.text\n                values[col_idx] = value\n            if max_col >= 0:\n                rows.append([values.get(i, '') for i in range(max_col + 1)])\n\n        text = '\\n'.join('\\t'.join(map(str, row)).rstrip() for row in rows if any(str(x).strip() for x in row))\n        print(text)", "reason": "Replaced pandas/openpyxl dependency with direct .xlsx parsing via zipfile and XML so the README sheet can be read in the sandbox without installing packages, and the code prints the extracted README content."}) [toolUseId=call_xR6J4vfKpOIZIzzfM9Nm0y4d]
